  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Benson Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "Proverbs 2:1-5",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Proverbs 2:1-5",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "My son, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "&c. — These words are spoken by Solomon, either, 1st, In the name of wisdom, as before: or rather, 2d, In his own name. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "If thou wilt hide my commandments with thee — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Wilt lay them up in thy mind and heart with care, as men do their choicest treasures; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "So that thou incline, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "&c. — Give thyself to the study of wisdom with affection and diligence. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Yea, if thou, criest after knowledge ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "— Namely, unto God, the only giver of it. Hebrew, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "אם לבינה תקרא",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "if thou callest to knowledge, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "that is, invitest it to come to thee; earnestly desirest its guidance; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "If thou seekest her as silver — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "With the same unwearied diligence and earnest desire, and patient expectation under all delays, disappointments, and difficulties, which the men of the world use in pursuit of riches, or in digging in mines of silver; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Then shalt thou understand — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "More perfectly and profitably; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "the fear of the Lord — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Which is the beginning of this wisdom, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Proverbs 1:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
