  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Henry's Concise Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "2:1-9 Those who earnestly seek heavenly wisdom, will never complain that they have lost their labour; and the freeness of the gift does not do away the necessity of our diligence, Joh 6:27. Let them seek, and they shall find it; let them ask, and it shall be given them. Observe who are thus favoured. They are the righteous, on whom the image of God is renewed, which consists in righteousness. If we depend upon God, and seek to him for wisdom, he will enable us to keep the paths of judgment.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Barnes' Notes on the Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Now in the divine order comes the promise ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Proverbs 2:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The conditions of its fulfillment are stated in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Proverbs 2:1-4",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " in four sets of parallel clauses, each with some shade of distinct meaning. Thus, not \"receiving\" only, but \"hiding\" or treasuring up - not the \"ear\" only, but the \"heart\" - not the mere \"cry,\" but the eager \"lifting up the voice.\" ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "CHAPTER 2",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Pr 2:1-22. Men are invited to seek wisdom because it teaches those principles by which they may obtain God's guidance and avoid the society and influence of the wicked, whose pernicious courses are described.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "1-5. Diligence in hearing and praying for instruction must be used to secure the great principle of godliness, the fear of God.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "hide … with thee—lay up in store (compare Pr 7:1).Solomon exhorteth his son to get Wisdom, Proverbs 2:1-4; telleth him the benefit he shall receive thereby, Proverbs 2:5-10, and the evils which he should avoid, Proverbs 2:11,12. The wicked man’s ways are described, Proverbs 2:13-20. A habitation promised the righteous, Proverbs 2:21. The end of the wicked miserable, Proverbs 2:22.  These words are spoken by Solomon, either, 1. In the name of wisdom, as before; or rather, 2. In his own name. Hide my commandments with thee; lay them up in thy mind and heart with care, as men do their choicest treasures. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "hide … with thee—lay up in store (compare Pr 7:1).Solomon exhorteth his son to get Wisdom, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Proverbs 2:1-4",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; telleth him the benefit he shall receive thereby, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Proverbs 2:5-10",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", and the evils which he should avoid, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Proverbs 2:11,12",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". The wicked man’s ways are described, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Proverbs 2:13-20",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". A habitation promised the righteous, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Proverbs 2:21",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". The end of the wicked miserable, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "bld",
            "text": "Proverbs 2:22",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "p",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " These words are spoken by Solomon, either, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "p",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "1. In the name of wisdom, as before; or rather, ",
